@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "MultiCon" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least 4
colours.

                             How to play?

  When first run, the MultiCon will briefly display a pattern just to show
where the links should be placed, after that, the game shuffles the links
and it is up to you to recreate that shape...

  To play, click on any octagonal-shaped tile, if there is at least one
link connected to the tile, it will rotate clockwise by 60 degrees around
that tile. Note that you cannot click on the small dots that are located
at various places on the game board. Sometimes, the small dots are placed
in such a way that they are part of the shape to match.

  A '@{b}?@{ub}' button appears on the lower left in the game window, clicking on
this button will briefly display the shape to match and then will
redisplay the game board as you left it.

  The colour of the links can be changed by clicking on the coloured star
button located on the lower right of the game board.

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button.

  Have fun!

@endnode

